"5:2:47" : {s: 5, a: 2, w: 47, r: "وقي", t: "وَٱتَّقُوا۟", l: "ٱتَّقَىٰ", lc: 166, tl: "wa-ittaqū", lb: "কোনো কিছুর ব্যাপারে অত্যন্ত সচেতন থাকা, আল্লাহর প্রতি সচেতন থাকা",e: "And fear", b: "এবং তোমরা ভয় কর", f: 38, rm: "to protect, save, preserve, ward off, guard against evil and calamity, be secure, take as a shield, regard the duty. muttaqii - one who guard against evil and against that which harms and injures and is regardful of his duty towards human beings and God."},
"5:2:48" : {s: 5, a: 2, w: 48, r: "اله", t: "ٱللَّهَ", l: "ٱللَّه", lc: 2811, tl: "l-laha", lb: "আল্লাহ ",e: "Allah", b: "আল্লাহকে", f: 592, rm: "to serve, worship or adore; to protect, grant refuge, preserve save, rescue, liberate; object of worship ie God; (ا-ل-ل-ه) God, the one true God applied as a proper name denoting the true god, comprising all the excellent divine names; a unity comprising all the essences of existing things."},
